### 1. `management/vision.md` — Product Vision

This file describes the product vision: who the target audience is, what value the product delivers to them, and a breakdown of value blocks.

Use this outline (adapt to what you know about this project from the existing AGENTS.md, README, and codebase):

```markdown
# Product Vision

## Target Audience

[Describe the primary users — who will use this product and why.]

## Value Proposition

[One or two sentences describing the core value the product delivers.]

## Value Blocks

### V1: [Value Block Name]

[Describe this block of value. What does it deliver to the user? Why is it important? This section will be referenced by specs.]

### V2: [Value Block Name]

[Describe this block of value...]

### VN: [Value Block Name]

[Describe this block of value...]
```

**Rules:**
- Value blocks should cover ALL the value the product aims to deliver.
- Use short, descriptive names for value blocks (e.g., "V1: User Authentication", "V2: Real-time Dashboard").
- Each value block must be independently understandable — assume specs will reference individual blocks.
- The content must be additive-only in the future. Never renumber value blocks after creation; always append new ones at the end.

